Package pkg_commands

  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    AleaCommand
    AleaCommand Class - Command only usable while in test mode, be sure to change the option in GameEngine before trying it.
    BackCommand
    BackCommand Class - Permits to back to the previous room the player was in
    ChargeCommand
    ChargeCommand Class - Permits to charge the Beamer inside a Room
    Command
    Command Class - Handles all the command side, a command is composed of two words (the command word and the argument word).
    CommandWords
    This class holds an enumeration table of all command words known to the game.
    DropCommand
    DropCommand Class - Permits to drop an item inside a Room
    EatCommand
    EatCommand Class - Permits player the eat for instance a cookie
    FireCommand
    FireCommand Class - Permits to fire the Beamer so it teleports you to a Room
    GoCommand
    GoCommand Class - Permits the player to move around the map, directions : north, south, east, west, up and down
    HelpCommand
    HelpCommand Class - Shows the help manual to the player
    InteractCommand
    TalkCommand Class - Permits the player to talk to an NPC
    InventoryCommand
    InventoryCommand Class - Shows user's inventory
    LoadCommand
    LoadCommand Class - Permits the player to load a savefile
    LookCommand
    LookCommand Class - Permits to either look inside the room, or look into a specific item (whether you give it an argument or not)
    QuitCommand
    QuitCommand Class - Permits to quit the game, shows a dialog right before, action depending on the choice
    SaveCommand
    SaveCommand Class - Permits the player to save the game
    TakeCommand
    TakeCommand Class - Permits player to take an item from a Room and to store it inside his inventory
    TalkCommand
    TalkCommand Class - Permits the player to talk to an NPC
    TestCommand
    TestCommand Class - Permits to test the game thanks to a txt file that has a specified path to follow upon commands
    UnknownCommand
    UnknownCommand Class - In case an unknown command has been entered by the user
  • Enum Summary 
    Enum Description
    CommandWord
    Representations for all the valid command words for the game.
